Definition: from {{h3344}}; a fire or fuel; abstractly, a conflagration; burning, hearth.
feminine of {{h4168}}; fuel; burning.
or מֻצָקָה; from {{h3332}}; properly, something poured out, i.e. a casting (of metal); by implication, a tube (as cast); when it was cast, pipe.
a primitive root; to jeer, i.e. (intens.) blaspheme; be corrupt.
or מוּצָק; from {{h3332}}; narrowness; figuratively, distress; anguish, is straitened, straitness.
from {{h5694}}; properly, fusion, i.e. literally, a casting (of metal); figuratively, a mass (of clay); casting, hardness.
the same as {{h4161}}; Motsa, the name of two Israelites; Moza.
feminine of {{h4161}}; (marg.; compare {{h6675}}); a family descent; also a sewer; draught house; going forth.
a primitive root; to press, i.e. (figuratively) to oppress; extortioner.

or מֹצָאxlit môtsâ corrected to môtsâʼ; from {{h3318}}; a going forth, i.e. (the act) an egress, or (the place) an exit; hence, a source or product; specifically, dawn, the rising of the sun (the East), exportation, utterance, a gate, a fountain, a mine, a meadow (as producing grass); brought out, bud, that which came out, east, going forth, goings out, that which (thing that) is gone out, outgoing, proceeded out, spring, vein, (water-) course (springs).
probably from an unused root meaning to gather in; a granary; garner.
or מֹפֵת; from {{h3302}} in the sense of conspicuousness; a miracle; by implication, a token or omen; miracle, sign, wonder(-ed at).
(Jeremiah 48:21) or מֵיפַעַת; or מֵפַעַת; from {{h3313}}; illuminative; Mophaath or Mephaath, a place in Palestine; Mephaath.
from {{h4151}} and {{h3050}}; assembly of Jah; Moadjah, an Israelite; Moadiah. Compare {{h4573}}.
from {{h3259}}; an appointed place, i.e. asylum; appointed.
from {{h3259}}; (as in {{h4150}}); properly, an assembly	figuratively, a troop; appointed time.

or מֹעֵד; or (feminine) מוֹעָדָה; (2 Chronicles 8:13), from {{h3259}}; properly, an appointment, i.e. a fixed time or season; specifically, a festival; conventionally a year; by implication, an assembly (as convened for a definite purpose); technically the congregation; by extension, the place of meeting; also a signal (as appointed beforehand); appointed (sign, time), (place of, solemn) assembly, congregation, (set, solemn) feast, (appointed, due) season, solemn(-ity), synogogue, (set) time (appointed).
from {{h5781}}; pressure, i.e. (figuratively) distress; affliction.
from {{h3289}}; a purpose; counsel, device.
from {{h5774}}; properly, covered, i.e. dark; abstractly, obscurity, i.e. distress; dimness.
feminine passive participle of {{h4571}}; properly, made to slip, i.e. dislocated; out of joint.
from {{h3245}}; a foundation; foundation.
feminine of {{h4143}}; a foundation; figuratively, an appointment; foundation, grounded. Compare {{h4328}}.
or מֹסָדָה; feminine of {{h4144}}; a foundation; foundation.
also (in plural) feminine מוֹסֵרָה; or מֹסְרָה; from {{h3256}}; properly, chastisement, i.e. (by implication) a halter; figuratively, restraint; band, bond.
from {{h3205}}; genitor; Molid, an Israelite; Molid.
from {{h5437}}; a turn, i.e. circuit (of a building); winding about.
or מֻסַבָּה; feminine of {{h4141}}; a reversal, i.e. the backside (of a gem), fold (of a double-leaved door), transmutation (of a name); being changed, inclosed, be set, turning.
from {{h3245}}; a foundation; foundation.

from {{h3256}}; properly, chastisement; figuratively, reproof, warning or instruction; also restraint; bond, chastening(-eth), chastisement, check, correction, discipline, doctrine, instruction, rebuke.
or (plural) מֹסְרוֹת feminine of {{h4147}}; correction or corrections; Moserah, a place in the Desert; Mosera.
a primitive root; to waver; by implication, to slip, shake, fall; be carried, cast, be out of course, be fallen in decay, × exceedingly, fall(-ing down), be (re-) moved, be ready, shake, slide, slip.
from {{h3045}}; acquaintance; kindred.
feminine of {{h4132}}; a pole; by implication, an ox-bow; hence, a yoke (either literal or figurative); bands, heavy, staves, yoke.
from {{h4131}}; a wavering, i.e. fall; by implication, a pole (as shaking); hence, a yoke (as essentially a bent pole); bar, be moved, staff, yoke.

a primitive root; to cut short, i.e. curtail (specifically the prepuce, i.e. to circumcise); by implication, to blunt; figuratively, to destroy; circumcise(-ing), selves), cut down (in pieces), destroy, × must needs.
a primitive root; to become thin, i.e. (figuratively) be impoverished; be (waxen) poor(-er).
from {{h3205}}; birth; Moladah, a place in Palestine; Moladah.

or מוֹל; (Deuteronomy 1:1), or מוֹאל; (Nehemiah 12:38), or מֻל; (Numbers 22:5), from {{h4135}}; properly, abrupt, i.e. a precipice; by implication, the front; used only adverbially (with prepositional prefix) opposite; (over) against, before, (fore-) front, from, (God-) ward, toward, with.
from {{h4135}}; circumcision; circumcision.
from {{h3205}}; nativity (plural birth-place); by implication, lineage, native country; also offspring, family; begotten, born, issue, kindred, native(-ity).

from {{h4118}} and {{h7998}} and {{h2363}} and {{h957}}; hasting (is he (the enemy) to the) booty, swift (to the) prey; Maher-Shalal-Chash-Baz; the symbolical name of the son of Isaiah; Maher-sha-lal-bash-baz.
from {{h2048}}; a delusion; deceit.
feminine of {{h4118}}; properly, a hurry; hence (adverbially) promptly; hastily, quickly, shortly, soon, make (with) speed(-ily), swiftly.
from {{h4116}}; hasty; Maharai, an Israelite; Maharai.
by transp. for {{h3996}}; an entrance; coming.
a primitive root; to melt, i.e. literally (to soften, flow down, disappear), or figuratively (to fear, faint); consume, dissolve, (be) faint(-hearted), melt (away), make soft.
from a prolonged form of the prepositional prefix m- and {{h1}}; from (her [the mother's]) father; Moab, an incestuous son of Lot; also his territory and descendants; Moab.
feminine מוֹאָבִיָּה; or מוֹאָבִיתxlit Môwâbîyth corrected to Môwʼâbîyth; patronymical from {{h4124}}; a Moabite or Moabitess, i.e. a descendant from Moab; (woman) of Moab, Moabite(-ish, -ss).
a primitive root; to shake; measure.
or rather מֹדָע; from {{h3045}}; an acquaintance; kinswoman.
from {{h4117}}; a price (for a wife); dowry.
from {{h4116}}; properly, hurrying; hence (adverbially) in a hurry; hasteth, hastily, at once, quickly, soon, speedily, suddenly.
a primitive root (perhaps rather the same as {{h4116}} through the idea of readiness in assent); to bargain (for a wife), i.e. to wed; endow, × surely.

a primitive root; properly, to be liquid or flow easily, i.e. (by implication); to hurry (in a good or a bad sense); often used (with another verb) adverbially, promptly; be carried headlong, fearful, (cause to make, in, make) haste(-n, -ily), (be) hasty, (fetch, make ready) × quickly, rash, × shortly, (be so) × soon, make speed, × speedily, × straightway, × suddenly, swift.
from {{h2015}}; a wrench, i.e. the stocks; prison, stocks.
from {{h2015}}; a destruction; when...overthrew, overthrow(-n).
from an unused root of uncertain meaning; perhaps an abyss; deep pit.
from {{h1986}}; a blow; stripe, stroke.
from {{h4110}} and {{h410}}; praise of God; Mahalalel, the name of an antediluvian patriarch and of an Israelite; Mahalaleel.
from {{h1984}}; fame; praise.
from an unused root meaning to mingle (water with wine); tempered wine; liquor.
from {{h2076}}; an altar; altar.
from {{h3498}}; literally gain; figuratively, superiority; plenteousness, preeminence, profit.
from {{h4191}}; death (natural or violent); concretely, the dead, their place or state (hades); figuratively, pestilence, ruin; (be) dead(-ly), death, die(-d).
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h4194}}; death; death.
(Psalm {{h48}} or מוּת לַבֵּן; from {{h4191}} and {{h1121}} with the preposition and article interposed; 'To die for the son', probably the title of a popular song; death, Muthlabben.

a primitive root; to die (literally or figuratively); causatively, to kill; × at all, × crying, (be) dead (body, man, one), (put to, worthy of) death, destroy(-er), (cause to, be like to, must) die, kill, necro(-mancer), × must needs, slay, × surely, × very suddenly, × in (no) wise.
from {{h3467}}; deliverance; salvation.
probably from an unused root meaning to faint with fear; terror; Mizzah, an Edomite; Mizzah.
from an unused root meaning to suck out; exhausted; burnt.
from {{h1980}}; a walking (plural collectively), i.e. access; place to walk.
from {{h1980}}; a walk, i.e. a passage or a distance; journey, walk.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h4100}}; how great (mighty), that which, what(-soever), why.
apparently a denominative from {{h4100}}; properly, to question or hesitate, i.e. (by implication) to be reluctant; delay, linger, stay selves, tarry.
from {{h1949}}; confusion or uproar; destruction, discomfiture, trouble, tumult, vexation, vexed.
of Persian origin; Mehuman, a eunuch of Xerxes; Mehuman.
from {{h3190}} (augmented) and {{h410}}; bettered of God; Mehetabel, the name of an Edomitish man and woman; Mehetabeel, Mehetabel.
or מָהִר; from {{h4116}}; quick; hence, skilful; diligent, hasty, ready.
a primitive root; properly, to cut down or reduce, i.e. by implication, to adulterate; mixed.
from {{h3423}}; a possession; figuratively, delight; possession, thought.
feminine of {{h4180}}; a possession; heritage, inheritance, possession.
from {{h3423}} and {{h1661}}; possession of Gath; Moresheth-Gath, a place in Palestine; Moresheth-gath.
patrial from {{h4182}}; a Morashtite or inhabitant of Moresheth-Gath; Morashthite.
a primitive root; to touch; feel, handle.

a primitive root (perhaps rather the same as {{h4184}} through the idea of receding by contact); to withdraw (both literally and figuratively, whether intransitive or transitive); cease, depart, go back, remove, take away.

or מֹשָׁב; from {{h3427}}; a seat; figuratively, a site; abstractly, a session; by extension an abode (the place or the time); by implication, population; assembly, dwell in, dwelling(-place), wherein (that) dwelt (in), inhabited place, seat, sitting, situation, sojourning.
or מֻשִּׁי; from {{h4184}}; sensitive; Mushi, a Levite; Mushi.
patronymical from {{h4187}}; a Mushite (collectively) or descendants of Mushi; Mushites.
act participle feminine of {{h4900}}; something drawing, i.e. (figuratively) a cord; band.
or מֹרִיָּה; from {{h7200}} and {{h3050}}; seen of Jah; Morijah, a hill in Palestine; Moriah.
from {{h3399}}; obstinate, i.e. independent; peeled.
from {{h3384}}; (see {{h3138}}); an archer; also teacher or teaching; also the early rain; (early) rain.
from {{h3381}}; a descent; as architecture, an ornamental appendage, perhaps a festoon; going down, steep place, thin work.
from {{h4171}} in the sense of shearing; a razor; razor.
or מֹרֶה; the same as {{h4175}}; Moreh, a Canaanite; also a hill (perhaps named from him); Moreh.
a primitive root; to alter; by implication, to barter, to dispose of; × at all, (ex-) change, remove.
or מֹקֵשׁ; from {{h3369}}; a noose (for catching animals) (literally or figuratively); by implication, a hook (for the nose); be ensnared, gin, (is) snare(-d), trap.
or מֹרַג; from an unused root meaning to triturate; a threshing sledge; threshing instrument.
or מֹרָא; or מוֹרָהxlit môrâh corrected to môwrâh; (Psalm 9:20), from {{h3372}}; fear; by implication, a fearful thing or deed; dread, (that ought to be) fear(-ed), terribleness, terror.
